 <purpose>This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the definition of topologically bounded surfaces. The face and edge geometry includes both elementary and free-form geometry.
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
  <li>3D geometry;</li>
  <li>B-spline curves and surfaces;</li>
  <li>conics;</li>
  <li>elementary curves;</li>
  <li>elementary surfaces;</li>
  <li>polylines;</li>
  <li>pcurves;</li>
  <li>sculptured surfaces;</li>
  <li>surface curves referencing pcurves;</li>
  <li>swept surfaces;</li>
  <li>twisted curves;</li>
  <li>unbounded geometry;</li>
  <li>geometric transformations;</li>
  <li>use of topology to bound geometric entities.</li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
  <li>2D geometry other than for the definition of a pcurve in the parameter
    space of a surface;</li>
  <li>bounded curves other than polylines and B-spline curves;</li>
  <li>bounded surfaces other than B-spline surfaces;</li>
  <li>offset curves and surfaces.</li>
 </outscope>
